analysisPopulations.name: Full Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The FAS will include all participants who are enrolled and receive at least one dose of BIVV001. Participants will be analyzed in the arm to which they were assigned.
analysisPopulations.label: FAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The FAS will include all participants who are enrolled and receive at least one dose of BIVV001. Participants will be analyzed in the arm to which they were assigned.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Enrolled AND received >=1 dose of BIVV001

analysisPopulations.name: Per-Protocol Set
analysisPopulations.text: The PPS will include all participants in the FAS who adhere to the protocol to a degree that their data are considered evaluable for the primary efficacy analysis. Criteria for exclusion from the PPS (e.g., major protocol deviations) will be finalized prior to database lock.
analysisPopulations.label: PPS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The PPS will include all participants in the FAS who adhere to the protocol to a degree that their data are considered evaluable for the primary efficacy analysis. Criteria for exclusion from the PPS (e.g., major protocol deviations) will be finalized prior to database lock.
analysisPopulations.criteria: FAS member AND no major protocol deviations

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The SAF will include all participants who receive at least one dose of BIVV001. Participants will be analyzed according to the treatment they actually received.
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The SAF will include all participants who receive at least one dose of BIVV001. Participants will be analyzed according to the treatment they actually received.

analysisPopulations.name: Pharmacokinetic Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The PKAS will include all participants who receive at least one dose of BIVV001 and have at least one evaluable PK sample.
analysisPopulations.label: PKAS
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The PKAS will include all participants who receive at least one dose of BIVV001 and have at least one evaluable PK sample.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received >=1 dose AND has >=1 evaluable PK sample

analysisPopulations.name: Surgery Subgroup
analysisPopulations.text: Participants from any arm who undergo major surgery during the study will be included in the surgery subgroup to assess control and prevention of bleeding with BIVV001 treatment in the surgical setting.
analysisPopulations.label: Surgery
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: Participants from any arm who undergo major surgery during the study will be included in the surgery subgroup to assess control and prevention of bleeding with BIVV001 treatment in the surgical setting.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Undergo major surgery during the study

characteristics.name: Endogenous FVIII activity
characteristics.description: Baseline endogenous FVIII activity level (severe defined as <1 IU/dL)
